  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Jews therefore said unto him that was cured,.... When they saw him, either at the place, or as he walked through the streets, with his bed on his back: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it is the sabbath day: do not you know it? surely you forget yourself, or you would never be guilty of such an action as this; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it is not lawful for thee to carry thy bed. It was forbid by the law, to carry any burden on the sabbath day; see Nehemiah 13:15; for ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "it is not lawful for thee to carry thy bed. It was forbid by the law, to carry any burden on the sabbath day; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 13:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; for ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"carrying out and bringing in anything, from one place to another, is said (x) to be work, and one of the principal works;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and therefore forbid by the law, which says, \"thou shall not do any work\"; and one of the traditions of the elders is this (y), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"whoever carries anything out (i.e. on the sabbath day), whether in his right hand, or in his left, in his bosom, or , \"on his shoulder\", is guilty; for so carried the Kohathites.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And particularly it is said (z), that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"he that rolls up a bed of the brasiers or tinkers (i.e. on the sabbath day) is bound to a sin offering.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which was a fold up bed, such as tinkers, and those that went from city to city to work, had; and who carried their beds with them, as the gloss observes; and were so far from being lawful to be carried by them, on the sabbath, that they might not fold them up. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(x) Maimon. Hilchot Sabbat, c. 12. sect. 6. (y) Misn. Sabbat, c. 10. sect. 3.((z) T. Bab. Sabbat, fol. 47. 1. & 138. 1.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(x) Maimon. Hilchot Sabbat, c. 12. sect. 6. (y) Misn. Sabbat, c. 10. sect. 3.((z) T. Bab. Sabbat, fol. 47. 1. & 138. 1.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
